Recently I wrote Senator Kay Hagan of NC expressing my position that there should be no new gun control in response to recent events.

The response received is below. While not committing to new gun control measures there is mention of "access to firearms" and talk of hunting. As we all know, we have numerous laws already controlling "access to firearms" and the 2nd amendment has nothing to do with hunting. Kay Hagan is a Democratic senator up for her first re-election in 2014 in a state where the governor's mansion and both houses of the General Assembly are now controlled by the GOP. Write and/or call Kay Hagan and tell her: " No more gun control." That means no 'ban' or NFA registration of "Assault weapons". No restrictions on the purchase of ammunition, no restriction on high capacity magazines, NO MORE GUN CONTROL. Instead we need police in the schools that don't already have them and better access control so just anyone cannot walk in off the street whenever they want. Magazine bans and ammunition bans have already been introduced in the house. Diane Feinstein has promised her "Assault weapons" ban which would require, among numerous other things, NFA registration and a $200 tax on "Assault Weapons" such as the AR-15 and pretty much anything that Diane thinks looks scary. New legislation will be introduced in the Senate on the 22nd.  Kay Hagan needs to hear loud and clear that more infringement of the 2nd amendment and more laws for criminals to ignore is not the solution to violence in America.

CHIAPPA 1911-22

The Chiappa 1911-22 model is a rimfire, semi-automatic pistol chambered in .22 LR. It is a straight blowback pistol in .22 Long Rifle only, with a fixed barrel solidly attached to the frame.

The Chiappa 1911 is constructed from Chiappalloy and steel components featuring wooden two piece grips. Polymer is used for the magazine catch, mainspring housing, non-rotating grip safety filler, and the body and follower of the 10-round single-column magazine.

It is the natural choice for semi-auto plinking, target shooting, and affordable handgun fun. Safety features include the traditional left-side thumb safety and a gun lock on the right rear side of the slide. A third safety feature is the guns automatic trigger safety, which blocks the trigger until the slide is fully forward into battery. Finally, the hammer features a half-cock notch. The front sight is a fixed sight and has been designed to allow extra material so that it can be filed to adjust for the individual shooter.

The Chiappa is a fixed barrel blow back design that maintains reliable functioning with minimal friction. The reliable return of the slide in combination w/ fixed front and rear sights maintans a constant return and quick, accurate follow-up shots. It includes two 10-rd magazines.

AWC VALKYRIE TI 22 SUPPRESSOR.

The Valkyrie TI is a super light-weight titanium suppressor. The AWC Valkyrie has an interchangeable rear mounting system, which allows you to swap between multiple host weapons regardless of thread pattern.

This is AWC's nicest titanium can, and it is made from solid titanium stock; it is not made from titanium tubing like others who use cheaper methods that don't give as nice of a build quality. This AWC model uses a solid welded fully machined blast baffle. Its forward purging design means gases cool faster while moving forward more efficiently.

The Valkyrie offers unbelievably accurate suppressed shooting. The Valkyrie is far and away the BEST 22 CAN ON THE MARKET and is of course also suited for the 17 HMR and 22 magnum in other firearms.
